Subtitle of Senate Bill 455
TO ALLOW REGULATION OF HEMP PRODUCTS BY ARKANSAS TOBACCO CONTROL;
AND TO AMEND THE UNIFORM CONTROLLED SUBSTANCES ACT TO REMOVE
CERTAIN SUBSTANCES THAT ARE DEFINED AS HEMP PRODUCTS.
______________________________________________________________________
Amendment No. 1 to Senate Bill 455
Amend Senate Bill 455 as originally introduced:
Page 5, delete line 9, and substitute the following:
"(a) A hemp product that is sold at retail in this state shall be sold
in a serving size that contains no more than fifty milligrams (50 mg) in the
aggregate of one (1) or more hemp-derived cannabinoids.
(b) Arkansas Tobacco Control shall regulate and enforce the
provisions"
AND
Page 5, line 11, delete "(b)" and substitute "(c)"
AND
Page 6, delete lines 3 through 7, and substitute the following:
"(a)(1) Hemp products in this state shall be tested by an ISO/IEC
17025 accredited testing laboratory that is accredited by a Global
Accreditation Cooperation Incorporated recognized accreditation body or an
equivalent body.
(2) The laboratory shall be accredited to the current ISO/IEC
17025 standard with the scope of the accreditation including hemp and hemp
products."
